OL,6,FChanges made by the Government to the
OL,7,FBill, in response to concerns raised
OL,8,Fin the Lords, included placing a duty
OL,9,Fon the regulator to avoid having a
OL,10,Fnegative impact on the financial
OL,11,Fgrowth of English football as well as
OL,12,Finvestment.
OL,14,FIt also introduced an amendment that
OL,15,Fwould make a club's contribution to
OL,16,Fthe economic and social well-being of
OL,17,Fits local community part of its
OL,18,Fcorporate governance.
